query.result:
1 When he who lights up the whole world 2 descends from our hemisphere, 3 so that daylight fades on every side,
4 the sky, which alone lights up with him first, 5 suddenly becomes visible again 6 through many lights, in which one shines;
7 and this action of the sky came to my mind, 8 like the sign of the world and its leaders 9 was silent in the blessed beak;
10 because all those living lights, 11 shining more brightly, began songs 12 that are faint and fleeting in my memory.

